1
00:00:38,970 --> 00:00:40,570
(All characters, places,
and organizations are fictional.)

2
00:00:40,570 --> 00:00:41,980
(Children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

3
00:00:44,110 --> 00:00:45,880
No way! This can't be happening!

4
00:00:46,980 --> 00:00:47,980
What's wrong, Mr. Ha?

5
00:00:53,790 --> 00:00:55,020
(Update 2: "Momo's mother, Hyun Ran Hee,
Suspected in Apparent Suicide")

6
00:00:57,990 --> 00:00:59,230
That's Geum Ba Ra for you.

7
00:00:59,230 --> 00:01:01,260
She's first on scene and gets top intel.
She's our rookie, too.

8
00:01:01,330 --> 00:01:02,860
What is going on?

9
00:01:03,000 --> 00:01:05,030
The secret engagement story just blew up.

10
00:01:05,100 --> 00:01:08,430
Gosh, someone's dying every day now.

11
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:09,500
The third update is out.

12
00:01:12,170 --> 00:01:13,170
Hurry up!

13
00:01:27,650 --> 00:01:29,720
Ma'am, it's dangerous.
Come on, what are you doing?

14
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:33,760
- Gosh, Chief!
- You're relentless. Seriously.

15
00:01:48,940 --> 00:01:51,480
(Unpo Police Station)

16
00:02:02,260 --> 00:02:03,260
Excuse me.

17
00:02:04,220 --> 00:02:06,530
Do you have someone to help
around the house?

18
00:02:07,830 --> 00:02:09,660
Who does the cleaning...

19
00:02:11,130 --> 00:02:13,430
Was it just you and your mother
living here?

20
00:02:19,670 --> 00:02:22,040
Shouldn't you have rushed her
to the hospital?

21
00:02:22,340 --> 00:02:24,580
You didn't even perform CPR.

22
00:02:25,710 --> 00:02:27,710
It was too late for CPR.

23
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:30,350
You just end up breaking their ribs
at that point.

24
00:02:36,420 --> 00:02:37,760
- Should we move her?
- Yes.

25
00:02:41,090 --> 00:02:43,360
Mom!

26
00:02:45,830 --> 00:02:47,130
- We're going in.
- You can't enter.

27
00:02:47,200 --> 00:02:48,530
We're close to her in both work and life.

28
00:02:48,530 --> 00:02:50,400
- If we can't go in, who can?
- Let us go in.

29
00:02:51,140 --> 00:02:52,140
We're practically family.

30
00:02:53,210 --> 00:02:55,340
- Who's in charge here?
- The police!

31
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:57,740
Just give us one comment!

32
00:02:57,740 --> 00:02:59,010
- Hey, let us through.
- Yes. sir.

33
00:03:02,880 --> 00:03:04,180
- Is that confirmed, Chief?
- Look over here!

34
00:03:04,250 --> 00:03:05,250
- Make way!
- Step back!

35
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:21,600
It's me.

36
00:03:25,400 --> 00:03:26,410
Are we sure it's a suicide?

37
00:03:26,710 --> 00:03:28,210
- Yes.
- Cause of death?

38
00:03:28,270 --> 00:03:30,640
- Hypothermia, most likely.
- Hypothermia?

39
00:03:30,710 --> 00:03:32,250
The bedroom's an absolute freezer.

40
00:03:32,380 --> 00:03:33,510
The AC was...

41
00:03:37,220 --> 00:03:38,550
This is not the time or place!

42
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:10,480
They're coming out!

43
00:04:32,710 --> 00:04:33,710
Momo.

44
00:04:55,390 --> 00:04:56,400
Hello.

45
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,800
You must be Momo's mother,
CEO Hyun Ran Hee.

46
00:05:11,380 --> 00:05:12,380
Ba Ra.

47
00:05:12,950 --> 00:05:14,810
- You actually came.
- Of course.

48
00:05:15,080 --> 00:05:16,220
Your mother is here too.

49
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:17,680
Goodness.

50
00:05:19,820 --> 00:05:20,890
Ms. Hyun.

51
00:05:21,590 --> 00:05:23,120
I didn't expect to see you here.

52
00:05:23,720 --> 00:05:24,820
Neither did I.

53
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:26,330
What brings you here?

54
00:05:26,590 --> 00:05:28,190
This is Geum Ba Ra,
a reporter from Sungwoo Daily.

55
00:05:29,430 --> 00:05:31,230
- Hello.
- Hello.

56
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:34,930
She's covering the exhibition today,
and my schedule just happened to be free.

57
00:05:37,340 --> 00:05:39,140
Are you close with CEO Ju Yeong Ae?

58
00:05:40,070 --> 00:05:42,610
No. My senior editor sent me to cover it.

59
00:05:42,810 --> 00:05:44,610
Mom, do you have an exhibition coming up?

60
00:05:44,610 --> 00:05:45,710
It's in the works.

61
00:05:46,010 --> 00:05:47,410
- That's Momo, right?
- Yes.

62
00:05:47,810 --> 00:05:49,350
She's so much prettier in person.

63
00:05:50,380 --> 00:05:51,380
I'll be back.

64
00:05:55,150 --> 00:05:56,820
Look at CEO Ju, schmoozing.

65
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:14,170
You can't just disappear on me
like last time.

66
00:06:15,140 --> 00:06:16,440
Chairman Kang has arrived.

67
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:17,540
- Welcome.
- It's my pleasure.

68
00:06:18,880 --> 00:06:19,910
Excuse me for a moment.

69
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:26,720
Hello.

70
00:06:29,190 --> 00:06:30,460
This is my daughter.

71
00:06:30,660 --> 00:06:33,260
Artist Paul Kim. He was based in Germany.

72
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:34,860
It's a pleasure to meet you.

73
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:36,960
Hello.

74
00:06:37,460 --> 00:06:40,100
Your pieces have already sold, you know.
Both of them.

75
00:06:42,940 --> 00:06:45,300
She's a close reporter friend of mine
from Sungwoo Daily.

76
00:06:47,910 --> 00:06:50,840
- Excuse me. Is Artist Paul Kim here?
- Yes.

77
00:06:51,540 --> 00:06:54,180
- That's him.
- How's your work coming along?

78
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:55,580
It's been a little slow lately.

79
00:06:56,280 --> 00:06:58,580
What do you do to relax?
Besides photography trips?

80
00:06:59,250 --> 00:07:00,890
I just read books and whatnot.

81
00:07:02,890 --> 00:07:04,290
Korea's changed a lot, hasn't it?

82
00:07:05,290 --> 00:07:07,290
Have you been back much?

83
00:07:07,630 --> 00:07:08,660
No.

84
00:07:09,530 --> 00:07:10,600
She doesn't look like you.

85
00:07:13,230 --> 00:07:14,970
An improvement on the original, right?

86
00:07:15,430 --> 00:07:17,970
I've never met her,
but I'm told I look like my grandmother.

87
00:07:19,970 --> 00:07:22,540
Excuse me, could I get a picture?

88
00:07:25,780 --> 00:07:26,910
Thank you.

89
00:07:28,110 --> 00:07:29,980
Give me a call next time you're in Seoul.

90
00:07:30,320 --> 00:07:31,480
You must be busy, though.

91
00:07:31,480 --> 00:07:33,320
It's fine as long as it's not last-minute.

92
00:07:35,790 --> 00:07:37,060
This is Artist Paul Kim.

93
00:07:38,590 --> 00:07:41,530
Hello. I'm Geum Ba Ra
from the Culture Desk at Sungwoo Daily.

94
00:07:43,000 --> 00:07:45,830
- Hi. I don't have a card yet.
- Please.

95
00:07:45,830 --> 00:07:47,700
Your work is your business card.

96
00:07:50,540 --> 00:07:52,340
Would you mind telling me a little
about your piece?

97
00:07:57,340 --> 00:07:58,510
Let me just get a picture first.

98
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:00,680
I'm not planning to run the story
right away.

99
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:07,820
You'll get fans after this photo gets out,
won't you?

100
00:08:36,820 --> 00:08:37,820
What about the suicide note?

101
00:08:40,650 --> 00:08:43,120
- The forensics team has it.
- What does it say?

102
00:08:50,330 --> 00:08:52,500
(Emergency Medical Center)

103
00:09:01,310 --> 00:09:03,040
- What happened?
- It appears to be a suicide.

104
00:09:03,110 --> 00:09:04,110
Okay, right this way.

105
00:10:52,620 --> 00:10:55,520
Ma'am, we're going to need you
to come down to the station.

106
00:10:59,730 --> 00:11:02,900
- We'll confirm with handwriting analysis.
- Understood.

107
00:11:02,960 --> 00:11:06,730
Check the gallery office, not the house,
for any documents handwritten by Ms. Hyun.

108
00:11:06,970 --> 00:11:08,000
Got it.

109
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:10,700
Let me see the suicide note.
I won't write it in the article.

110
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:13,210
You've already gotten your scoop.

111
00:11:16,840 --> 00:11:17,880
Go in my office.

112
00:11:17,880 --> 00:11:19,310
Reporters will be
swarming in here any minute.

113
00:11:23,250 --> 00:11:26,690
I can't imagine how you're feeling,
but we need to get your statement.

114
00:11:29,460 --> 00:11:31,220
Can you walk us through what happened?

115
00:11:31,860 --> 00:11:33,490
What time did you find her?

116
00:11:35,460 --> 00:11:36,700
I don't know.

117
00:11:37,230 --> 00:11:40,600
I didn't have anything scheduled today,
so I slept in a little.

118
00:11:44,600 --> 00:11:45,770
And when I woke up,

119
00:11:48,040 --> 00:11:49,240
it was quiet,

120
00:11:50,480 --> 00:11:52,410
so I figured she had gone to the gallery.

121
00:11:59,890 --> 00:12:02,490
How'd you know to call?
I literally just walked in.

122
00:12:03,560 --> 00:12:04,790
James just told me.

123
00:12:05,390 --> 00:12:06,690
Do you have plans for Christmas Eve?

124
00:12:06,690 --> 00:12:08,190
You know I don't make any special plans.

125
00:12:08,590 --> 00:12:10,800
I always have dinner with you
on Christmas Eve.

126
00:12:11,900 --> 00:12:13,570
We're thicker than blood, I swear.

127
00:12:13,700 --> 00:12:15,300
Does just sharing blood make you family?

128
00:12:15,470 --> 00:12:16,470
Exactly.

129
00:12:17,040 --> 00:12:18,640
Because plenty of siblings
are worse than strangers.

130
00:12:18,700 --> 00:12:19,870
(Hospital Director, Shin Ju Shin)

131
00:12:19,940 --> 00:12:21,210
You should do a talent donation this time.

132
00:12:21,910 --> 00:12:23,280
What talent do I even have?

133
00:12:23,340 --> 00:12:26,280
Perform at the Sponsor Appreciation Night
at Nua Children's Home.

134
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:27,550
My fingers are stiff now.

135
00:12:27,610 --> 00:12:29,010
They'll loosen up if you practice.

136
00:12:29,680 --> 00:12:31,150
It'd be great if James could come too.

137
00:12:31,380 --> 00:12:33,350
(Auditorium)

138
00:12:33,420 --> 00:12:34,650
Come on, let's go.

139
00:12:39,730 --> 00:12:42,060
- Hello.
- We keep running into each other.

140
00:12:42,160 --> 00:12:44,500
- It's not over, is it?
- Part two is about to start.

141
00:12:45,430 --> 00:12:48,500
(Nua Children's Home
Sponsor Appreciation Night)

142
00:12:53,210 --> 00:12:54,940
- Thank you.
- I'm a huge fan.

143
00:12:59,510 --> 00:13:01,280
- Hello.
- Hello.

144
00:13:01,680 --> 00:13:03,020
Are you enjoying the food?

145
00:13:18,230 --> 00:13:21,230
(Nua General Hospital)

146
00:13:22,430 --> 00:13:24,100
Do you come to this every year?

147
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:25,640
Yes.

148
00:13:28,170 --> 00:13:31,080
The vibe here is so great with the music.

149
00:13:34,680 --> 00:13:36,010
You're drinking quite a bit today.

150
00:13:36,920 --> 00:13:37,950
It's Christmas Eve.

151
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:40,650
Next year, I'll keep my schedule clear,

152
00:13:40,650 --> 00:13:42,960
come early, and have a meal with the kids.

153
00:13:43,490 --> 00:13:44,490
You definitely should.

154
00:13:59,170 --> 00:14:00,570
(Nua Children's Home
Sponsor Appreciation Night)

155
00:15:54,190 --> 00:15:55,750
(Nua Children's Home
Sponsor Appreciation Night)

156
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:25,920
(Nua Children's Home)

157
00:16:37,760 --> 00:16:39,060
(Nua Children's Home)

158
00:16:39,130 --> 00:16:40,870
- How'd the surgery go?
- It went well.

159
00:16:40,870 --> 00:16:43,240
The Chairman is on a call
with Ambassador Yu Gu Jong.

160
00:16:43,240 --> 00:16:45,300
All right. Is Momo here yet?

161
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:47,810
Yes, she's a big hit with our guests.

162
00:16:51,980 --> 00:16:53,310
I'm so jealous.

163
00:16:53,380 --> 00:16:55,910
(Nua Children's Home
Sponsor Appreciation Night)

164
00:17:03,120 --> 00:17:04,220
You're here.

165
00:17:04,560 --> 00:17:06,930
- Advisor.
- Where's your father?

166
00:17:08,890 --> 00:17:10,760
- Advisor!
- What is it?

167
00:17:10,830 --> 00:17:12,300
- What's going on?
- Advisor!

168
00:17:19,170 --> 00:17:20,640
Are you adopting another one?

169
00:17:22,910 --> 00:17:23,910
No.

170
00:17:25,040 --> 00:17:27,910
- It's not been long since Oiji passed.
- Where are you?

171
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:29,750
Here.

172
00:17:34,020 --> 00:17:36,120
I thought you'd be pulling an all-nighter
with Ju Shin.

173
00:17:36,420 --> 00:17:38,320
Momo's sponsored by your company, right?

174
00:17:38,620 --> 00:17:40,590
- Yes.
- Introduce me.

175
00:17:40,660 --> 00:17:42,460
- Was Momo at the party too?
- Yes.

176
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:46,400
Forget about it.
She's getting engaged to Ju Shin soon.

177
00:17:48,830 --> 00:17:49,840
Really?

178
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:51,240
Yes.

179
00:17:53,540 --> 00:17:56,710
- Did you introduce them?
- Ju Shin is head over heels for her.

180
00:17:57,110 --> 00:18:00,850
That's why Momo's here.
She'll be the foundation's first lady.

181
00:18:04,080 --> 00:18:06,590
Go have a cold beer to cool off
instead of just water.

182
00:18:08,790 --> 00:18:10,020
How are things between you and Eun Ah?

183
00:18:14,630 --> 00:18:17,300
Of all people, Momo?
I'm on Team Geum Ba Ra.

184
00:18:42,390 --> 00:18:43,390
Hello.

185
00:18:48,360 --> 00:18:49,360
It's cold out here.

186
00:18:49,860 --> 00:18:51,160
It's too hot inside.

187
00:18:52,560 --> 00:18:55,870
I made a fool of myself the other day.
I didn't know you were Ju Shin's friend.

188
00:18:57,140 --> 00:18:59,810
I got carried away hearing live music
for the first time in a while.

189
00:19:01,710 --> 00:19:02,840
Do you have a side gig?

190
00:19:04,110 --> 00:19:05,510
I'm not good enough to moonlight.

191
00:19:06,580 --> 00:19:08,410
I'm so jealous of people
who can play an instrument.

192
00:19:09,050 --> 00:19:11,720
- You could just learn.
- Then you can tutor me part-time.

193
00:19:15,750 --> 00:19:16,860
Where's Ju Shin?

194
00:19:17,620 --> 00:19:19,830
- The restroom.
- Is his stomach acting up again?

195
00:19:20,130 --> 00:19:23,060
Yes.
And he only had juice on the way over.

196
00:19:24,160 --> 00:19:25,760
I guess that's
how the skies keep things fair.

197
00:19:25,760 --> 00:19:27,430
Ju Shin has a weak stomach,

198
00:19:28,170 --> 00:19:29,700
but he's an A-plus in every other way.

199
00:19:33,740 --> 00:19:34,840
I'm Ha Yong Joong, by the way.

200
00:19:35,210 --> 00:19:39,480
With the Advisor collapsing that day,
Ju Shin never got to introduce us.

201
00:19:41,010 --> 00:19:42,110
I'm Momo.

202
00:19:42,110 --> 00:19:44,750
I looked you up. It's your real name.

203
00:19:45,420 --> 00:19:47,920
Yes,
a lot of people assume it's a stage name.

204
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:51,190
So why did you look me up?

205
00:19:54,860 --> 00:19:56,030
Curious about me as an actress?

206
00:19:57,800 --> 00:19:59,360
Or as your friend's girlfriend?

207
00:20:02,330 --> 00:20:04,270
Both, of course.

208
00:20:09,140 --> 00:20:10,910
I hear you've been very busy.

209
00:20:11,240 --> 00:20:14,150
I was away for a while,
so I have a lot to catch up on.

210
00:20:14,350 --> 00:20:17,420
Everyone's been swamped.
Especially Ju Shin, of course.

211
00:20:19,320 --> 00:20:20,390
Ju Shin...

212
00:20:21,350 --> 00:20:23,360
never really showed much interest
in women before.

213
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:27,030
I even started to wonder
if he had a crush on me.

214
00:20:38,540 --> 00:20:39,540
It's all set.

215
00:20:41,310 --> 00:20:42,310
What do you mean?

216
00:20:44,640 --> 00:20:45,810
You seem happy.

217
00:20:49,350 --> 00:20:50,780
Do you have any jinxes, by any chance?

218
00:20:51,850 --> 00:20:52,980
What kind of jinx?

219
00:20:52,980 --> 00:20:54,850
The kind that makes you want to dance.

220
00:20:55,550 --> 00:20:57,260
If only music were playing now...

221
00:20:57,620 --> 00:20:59,720
I have the sudden urge to waltz right now.

222
00:21:03,330 --> 00:21:04,330
With me?

223
00:21:06,260 --> 00:21:07,270
Yes.

224
00:21:58,450 --> 00:22:01,450
Spring is right around the corner,
and yet a blizzard hit us.

225
00:22:02,290 --> 00:22:03,690
You know how to waltz?

226
00:22:04,860 --> 00:22:05,890
I am an actress, after all.

227
00:22:06,760 --> 00:22:08,260
I can sort of pull off the tango too.

228
00:22:09,160 --> 00:22:12,160
I wish I'd learned it
for a day like today.

229
00:22:14,630 --> 00:22:17,170
I heard your mother was
a double bass player.

230
00:22:17,640 --> 00:22:18,640
She was.

231
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:20,840
Ju Shin...

232
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:23,580
didn't just say good things about me,
did he?

233
00:22:24,940 --> 00:22:26,750
He said you were
his most troublesome friend.

234
00:22:33,420 --> 00:22:35,320
Is my makeup too much?

235
00:22:37,090 --> 00:22:38,090
No.

236
00:22:48,530 --> 00:22:49,670
Why are you standing out here?

237
00:22:52,500 --> 00:22:54,310
It's hot in this dress.

238
00:22:56,370 --> 00:22:59,140
(Our deepest condolences
to the bereaved family)

239
00:23:29,210 --> 00:23:30,210
(Family waiting room)

240
00:23:38,920 --> 00:23:40,950
Push my meeting with Mr. Jo to tomorrow.

241
00:23:41,690 --> 00:23:44,060
- The cross shoot is at 3 p.m.
- Send Manager Choi.

242
00:23:45,090 --> 00:23:47,790
- Let's go pay our respects, Jin Ju.
- I've already been.

243
00:23:48,130 --> 00:23:50,230
- When?
- Last night.

244
00:23:56,840 --> 00:23:57,840
Momo.

245
00:23:59,100 --> 00:24:00,270
Did I do the right thing?

246
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:02,840
Do I really have to let you go like this?

247
00:25:15,980 --> 00:25:17,120
Do you think you'll be able to sleep?

248
00:25:18,420 --> 00:25:20,490
Just talk to me like you talk to Momo.

249
00:25:20,890 --> 00:25:22,090
If anyone heard you...

250
00:25:22,450 --> 00:25:24,060
It's not like we'll be seeing each other
much longer anyway.

251
00:25:29,690 --> 00:25:32,030
You can say you broke up naturally
by next year anyway.

252
00:25:35,000 --> 00:25:36,000
Go.

253
00:25:38,340 --> 00:25:40,310
I'm going to keep drinking
until I fall asleep.

254
00:25:42,370 --> 00:25:44,240
I'm really starting to feel
like I'm becoming Momo.

255
00:25:44,940 --> 00:25:48,550
She's not some stranger.
She's my own flesh and blood.

256
00:25:49,350 --> 00:25:52,680
I am Momo, and Momo is me.

257
00:25:56,250 --> 00:25:57,760
Puppies and wine...

258
00:25:58,320 --> 00:26:00,330
are the deity's gift to humanity.

259
00:26:06,930 --> 00:26:07,930
You're not having any?

260
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:09,370
I drove.

261
00:26:09,630 --> 00:26:10,940
We can call for a ride.

262
00:26:15,170 --> 00:26:16,470
When I look in the mirror,

263
00:26:16,880 --> 00:26:18,810
it doesn't feel like Momo's dead.

264
00:26:19,910 --> 00:26:24,050
It just feels like
I'm looking right at my daughter.

265
00:26:27,490 --> 00:26:28,850
Hyun Ran Hee is the one who died.

266
00:26:31,320 --> 00:26:32,990
They say there's more than meets the eye,

267
00:26:33,530 --> 00:26:35,560
you should just accept what you see.

268
00:26:36,230 --> 00:26:37,900
There's no need to overthink it.

269
00:26:45,440 --> 00:26:46,740
It's too quiet.

270
00:26:51,910 --> 00:26:54,180
He has such a noble brow.

271
00:26:54,880 --> 00:26:56,750
So aristocratic.

272
00:26:57,250 --> 00:26:58,980
Like fine white porcelain.

273
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:02,720
Leaving?

274
00:27:06,930 --> 00:27:08,430
Loosen your tie before you go.

275
00:27:08,760 --> 00:27:10,360
It looks so tight and suffocating.

276
00:27:39,520 --> 00:27:40,890
Go abroad for a while.

277
00:27:41,660 --> 00:27:42,660
It's me.

278
00:27:45,930 --> 00:27:47,130
Why on earth?

279
00:27:48,230 --> 00:27:49,900
(CEO James Ha)

280
00:27:51,840 --> 00:27:54,570
- Hello?
- Hi, it's James.

281
00:27:54,770 --> 00:27:56,070
Mr. Ha. Hello.

282
00:27:56,270 --> 00:28:00,110
With Momo's mother away,
I'm sure you don't have an appetite.

283
00:28:00,310 --> 00:28:02,480
I figured you'd be starving at home alone,

284
00:28:02,550 --> 00:28:04,020
so I made some side dishes.

285
00:28:04,820 --> 00:28:08,020
Sending them by a manager felt impersonal,
and I was worried about you.

286
00:28:08,850 --> 00:28:09,850
I see.

287
00:28:10,560 --> 00:28:12,720
Would it be alright if I dropped by?

288
00:28:13,120 --> 00:28:15,660
They aren't dishes we have to eat today,
are they?

289
00:28:15,730 --> 00:28:16,960
Of course not.

290
00:28:17,230 --> 00:28:18,560
Are you on your way home?

291
00:28:18,930 --> 00:28:20,300
Are you off work yet?

292
00:28:20,600 --> 00:28:21,700
I'm about to.

293
00:28:23,130 --> 00:28:24,140
Have a seat.

294
00:28:26,770 --> 00:28:28,640
Do you have any food at home?

295
00:28:29,440 --> 00:28:31,880
I'm not that interested in food.

296
00:28:32,540 --> 00:28:36,350
Why not? Eating is extremely important.

297
00:28:38,180 --> 00:28:39,680
That's no good.

298
00:28:39,680 --> 00:28:42,150
Eat well in your youth to age well.

299
00:28:42,250 --> 00:28:45,960
- Hippocrates said it best.
- "You are what you eat"?

300
00:28:46,020 --> 00:28:47,030
Exactly.

301
00:28:50,860 --> 00:28:52,400
Do you have a dog?

302
00:28:53,260 --> 00:28:55,100
I lost her, the year before last.

303
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:03,210
Do you like dogs?

304
00:29:03,810 --> 00:29:05,010
Of course.

305
00:29:05,840 --> 00:29:07,450
Her name was Oiji?

306
00:29:08,150 --> 00:29:09,680
They give out awards for this?

307
00:29:10,420 --> 00:29:11,450
Yes.

308
00:29:11,650 --> 00:29:13,920
She had been through a lot.

309
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:27,630
I think I taste some lemon.

310
00:29:27,700 --> 00:29:29,700
That, and some other healthy stuff.

311
00:29:30,030 --> 00:29:31,470
Stay for a quick dinner.

312
00:29:31,700 --> 00:29:34,710
- No, I'm fine.
- It's no trouble. It's already made.

313
00:30:02,530 --> 00:30:05,800
It's not from a package.
I slow-cooked it with premium beef.

314
00:30:05,940 --> 00:30:07,410
You're so busy, but you made it yourself?

315
00:30:07,470 --> 00:30:09,270
They say, "If you want it done right,
do it yourself."

316
00:30:10,170 --> 00:30:11,410
I've heard that one.

317
00:30:11,910 --> 00:30:13,080
Add salt if you need it.

318
00:30:17,880 --> 00:30:19,050
Thank you for the meal.

319
00:30:24,920 --> 00:30:26,620
- It's not bland at all.
- Good.

320
00:30:26,620 --> 00:30:28,660
It's perfect. I actually prefer less salt.

321
00:30:28,730 --> 00:30:30,660
That's the way to do it.

322
00:30:37,240 --> 00:30:39,570
Wouldn't it be nice to live this way?

323
00:30:39,570 --> 00:30:41,240
I'd treat her like a queen,

324
00:30:41,310 --> 00:30:43,140
and she wouldn't have to lift a finger.

325
00:30:48,580 --> 00:30:50,750
Gosh, look how she enjoys her food.

326
00:30:52,850 --> 00:30:55,720
She didn't seem depressed at all.

327
00:30:56,350 --> 00:31:00,260
Right. Maybe if her career
as Momo was failing...

328
00:31:00,760 --> 00:31:03,930
- She was about to get married...
- I know.

329
00:31:03,930 --> 00:31:05,100
She had a top-star daughter,

330
00:31:05,160 --> 00:31:07,800
who was engaged to a catch
like Director Shin,

331
00:31:07,800 --> 00:31:09,200
and her gallery was doing well.

332
00:31:09,470 --> 00:31:11,670
Do you think having no worries
is a problem in itself?

333
00:31:13,100 --> 00:31:14,540
How is Momo getting by?

334
00:31:17,210 --> 00:31:18,210
By the way,

335
00:31:18,540 --> 00:31:21,710
since you're Yong Joong's older brother,
you don't have to be so formal with me.

336
00:31:22,750 --> 00:31:24,780
- You sure?
- Yes.

337
00:31:24,850 --> 00:31:27,350
That makes sense,
since you're so close with Yong Joong.

338
00:31:29,020 --> 00:31:30,960
Maybe she'll feel that way with me.

339
00:31:32,620 --> 00:31:35,560
- Ha Yong Joong's car is now arriving.
- He's here for the side dishes.

340
00:31:36,790 --> 00:31:39,260
It's all the same stuff, so take one each.

341
00:31:39,560 --> 00:31:43,470
- One for me too?
- They're better if you make a big batch.

342
00:31:43,600 --> 00:31:46,000
I'll drop Ba Ra off and take this to Momo.

343
00:31:46,500 --> 00:31:47,510
And why would you do that?

344
00:31:47,970 --> 00:31:50,340
- Does Ba Ra even have her car here?
- She can take a cab.

345
00:31:50,640 --> 00:31:51,640
Right?

346
00:31:52,580 --> 00:31:54,650
You're going to make a reporter
run errands for an actress?

347
00:31:54,710 --> 00:31:57,010
Their jobs have nothing to do with it.
They were close friends.

348
00:31:57,520 --> 00:31:58,580
Weren't you?

349
00:32:00,120 --> 00:32:03,860
- Anyway.
- She's alone at home with no helper.

350
00:32:04,090 --> 00:32:06,090
I can just ask her
to come down to the lobby.

351
00:32:06,320 --> 00:32:10,060
Is Momo just some random person?
What if Ju Shin gets the wrong idea?

352
00:32:10,130 --> 00:32:12,360
It could get awkward for Momo too.

353
00:32:12,700 --> 00:32:14,230
It's just an errand for you.
What's the big deal?

354
00:32:14,930 --> 00:32:17,970
I didn't ask you to. Leave me out of it.
Fine then.

355
00:32:18,770 --> 00:32:20,440
I'll just eat it myself then. Forget it.

356
00:32:21,710 --> 00:32:24,210
I think he's just worried about her.

357
00:32:24,580 --> 00:32:26,340
That's my point.

358
00:32:26,340 --> 00:32:28,550
Why is he so worried
about his best friend's fiancee?

359
00:32:28,610 --> 00:32:30,550
Ju Shin will take care of her.

360
00:32:30,550 --> 00:32:32,120
You think Ju Shin cooks and cleans?

361
00:32:32,420 --> 00:32:33,550
You think he has time?

362
00:32:33,550 --> 00:32:35,190
- If he had three bodies...
- And you?

363
00:32:35,520 --> 00:32:36,550
Do you have time?

364
00:32:36,620 --> 00:32:38,290
Imagine how hard it must be
for her right now.

365
00:32:39,220 --> 00:32:40,630
We went through it too.

366
00:32:41,430 --> 00:32:42,430
Have you forgotten?

367
00:32:46,900 --> 00:32:49,200
Let's go see her tomorrow morning.

368
00:32:49,430 --> 00:32:51,240
I can't just ignore this either.

369
00:32:51,570 --> 00:32:53,400
It's too late tonight.

370
00:33:06,450 --> 00:33:07,450
Her address.

371
00:33:14,860 --> 00:33:16,060
You don't get it either, do you?

372
00:33:31,810 --> 00:33:33,980
Sorry, all I have is water and coffee.

373
00:33:35,950 --> 00:33:37,050
I'm thirsty.

374
00:33:51,300 --> 00:33:52,300
That guy...

375
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:54,570
He's been doing better than I expected.

376
00:33:57,070 --> 00:33:58,840
Being a bodyguard pays pretty well.

377
00:34:00,270 --> 00:34:01,470
It's hazard pay.

378
00:34:04,080 --> 00:34:06,080
Once I get the new place,
I'll sell this place...

379
00:34:06,080 --> 00:34:08,080
and donate the money in An Hee's name.

380
00:34:09,850 --> 00:34:11,550
You know I can help you out.

381
00:34:14,690 --> 00:34:16,390
Am I treating you differently from An Hee?

382
00:34:18,060 --> 00:34:20,890
I've faced so much discrimination,
I don't want to even hear that word.

383
00:34:24,560 --> 00:34:26,230
Lawyer Tae Won Young said he knew you.

384
00:34:28,970 --> 00:34:30,530
I signed a contract with his law firm,

385
00:34:31,070 --> 00:34:32,570
and while we were talking
about that interview article...

386
00:34:35,670 --> 00:34:37,610
I heard he got remarried.

387
00:34:39,610 --> 00:34:40,810
Is he happy?

388
00:34:41,310 --> 00:34:42,380
He's remarried?

389
00:34:43,380 --> 00:34:46,050
- What did he say about me?
- Nothing really.

390
00:34:46,050 --> 00:34:47,990
An associate was there.

391
00:34:48,390 --> 00:34:49,690
Do you two have some kind of history?

392
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:07,440
Are you Ye Jeong's father?

393
00:35:07,470 --> 00:35:08,510
Yes.

394
00:35:10,240 --> 00:35:11,480
I'm here because of Ye Jeong.

395
00:35:12,610 --> 00:35:14,810
I was on my way to the police station,
but I came here instead.

396
00:35:18,280 --> 00:35:19,320
Ye Jeong!

397
00:35:20,350 --> 00:35:22,720
Your father said
he was going to bed early.

398
00:35:22,790 --> 00:35:24,020
Tell her to come downstairs.

399
00:35:35,400 --> 00:35:36,400
Sit.

400
00:35:39,100 --> 00:35:40,500
Let's talk about this inside.

401
00:35:46,010 --> 00:35:47,580
- I'm home, Father.
- Alright.

402
00:35:49,580 --> 00:35:50,580
Who are you?

403
00:35:52,880 --> 00:35:54,190
My name is Geum Ba Ra.

404
00:35:54,720 --> 00:35:56,550
I'm not in the same class
as Tae Ye Jeong, though.

405
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:06,230
Sit down, all of you.

406
00:36:08,070 --> 00:36:09,570
Bring something out.

407
00:36:10,170 --> 00:36:11,170
I'm fine.

408
00:36:16,440 --> 00:36:18,680
I grew up at an orphanage...

409
00:36:18,680 --> 00:36:20,480
with a girl from my class, Kim Jin Ju.

410
00:36:21,210 --> 00:36:23,350
Do you know Nua Children's Home?

411
00:36:23,750 --> 00:36:25,650
The one behind the cathedral?

412
00:36:26,020 --> 00:36:29,990
Yes. Jin Ju and I have been roommates
our whole lives,

413
00:36:30,520 --> 00:36:32,890
but Tae Ye Jeong constantly bullies her.

414
00:36:32,890 --> 00:36:35,460
Today, she even hit her with two others.

415
00:36:38,130 --> 00:36:40,260
- It's over and done with.
- How can it be over?

416
00:36:40,330 --> 00:36:41,430
I ended it.

417
00:36:41,530 --> 00:36:43,330
But you're the one
who started this up again.

418
00:36:43,900 --> 00:36:46,200
- I got hit too!
- Quiet!

419
00:36:48,040 --> 00:36:49,770
I saw the three of them
ganging up on Jin Ju,

420
00:36:49,840 --> 00:36:52,840
so I had no choice but to hit them
a few times to defend her.

421
00:36:53,510 --> 00:36:55,650
They started coming after me too.
What was I supposed to do?

422
00:36:56,250 --> 00:36:58,250
Growing up in an orphanage
is already hard enough,

423
00:36:58,680 --> 00:37:00,250
and it's a painful wound.

424
00:37:02,090 --> 00:37:05,520
But they ridiculed us,
calling us brats with no parents.

425
00:37:06,490 --> 00:37:08,330
But I endured it and put an end to it.

426
00:37:10,090 --> 00:37:13,160
Did you know your daughter bullies kids
who are easy targets?

427
00:37:15,400 --> 00:37:16,430
I didn't even...

428
00:37:17,370 --> 00:37:18,670
That's not what a student does.

429
00:37:18,900 --> 00:37:21,240
She does monstrous things
without a second thought.

430
00:37:21,510 --> 00:37:24,680
Have you ever thought about what it's like
to be on the receiving end?

431
00:37:24,680 --> 00:37:25,680
You're lying.

432
00:37:27,010 --> 00:37:28,880
- Don't exaggerate.
- You think I'm exaggerating?

433
00:37:29,280 --> 00:37:30,280
So...

434
00:37:30,610 --> 00:37:33,780
Are you saying my Ye Jeong
did this to you?

435
00:37:35,290 --> 00:37:36,350
Her "husband" did.

436
00:37:36,790 --> 00:37:37,790
Hey!

437
00:37:39,760 --> 00:37:41,690
It's just a stupid joke
among the kids at school.

438
00:37:41,760 --> 00:37:43,460
I heard it clearly. Yoon Seong Tae.

439
00:37:43,460 --> 00:37:44,760
He's a senior at our school,

440
00:37:44,930 --> 00:37:46,700
and he said,
"You scratched my wife's face."

441
00:37:46,700 --> 00:37:47,730
What...

442
00:37:47,730 --> 00:37:48,800
Father.

443
00:37:51,800 --> 00:37:53,970
He's just an older guy
who tends to overreact.

444
00:37:54,840 --> 00:37:56,270
Is doing this to me "overreacting?"

445
00:37:56,640 --> 00:37:59,480
So those guys you know just kidnapped me
as a group because they were bored?

446
00:37:59,640 --> 00:38:00,740
And then did this to me?

447
00:38:02,380 --> 00:38:04,950
- You provoked them!
- I don't know what you told them,

448
00:38:05,720 --> 00:38:06,850
but they completely lost it.

449
00:38:07,320 --> 00:38:08,920
Did you or did you not hear...

450
00:38:08,920 --> 00:38:10,120
four senior boys screaming
that I scratched your face...

451
00:38:10,120 --> 00:38:12,420
as they began to strip me and beat me?

452
00:38:13,190 --> 00:38:15,490
You were smiling, encouraging them
to "teach me a real lesson."

453
00:38:16,390 --> 00:38:18,100
Tae Ye Jeong hit me over the head
with a piece of lumber.

454
00:38:18,360 --> 00:38:20,130
Come feel my head and see how bad it is.

455
00:38:20,930 --> 00:38:22,430
You... You little...

456
00:38:22,700 --> 00:38:25,270
Did you not know your daughter was running
around doing things like this?

457
00:38:28,670 --> 00:38:29,670
Say something!

458
00:38:30,670 --> 00:38:31,680
I'm sorry.

459
00:38:33,010 --> 00:38:34,850
- Go to your room.
- No.

460
00:38:35,780 --> 00:38:37,310
I'm not done talking yet.

461
00:38:39,020 --> 00:38:40,120
I...

462
00:38:40,850 --> 00:38:42,190
know how to fight.

463
00:38:42,650 --> 00:38:45,020
For self-defense,
so I wouldn't just get beaten up.

464
00:38:46,120 --> 00:38:48,230
If I hadn't held back with every ounce
of my strength today,

465
00:38:49,030 --> 00:38:50,790
Tae Ye Jeong would be
in a full-body cast right now.

466
00:38:52,460 --> 00:38:53,700
Big deal.

467
00:38:54,430 --> 00:38:55,870
You always go around dropping
your dad's name, don't you?

468
00:38:56,600 --> 00:38:58,070
Saying he's a lawyer
at a big firm in Seoul.

469
00:38:58,570 --> 00:38:59,940
So who's going to sue you
after you beat them up?

470
00:39:00,770 --> 00:39:03,270
I know.
Teachers walk on eggshells around you.

471
00:39:04,310 --> 00:39:06,640
And you've got top thug Yoon Seong Tae
as your "husband."

472
00:39:06,640 --> 00:39:08,410
He's not my husband, you witch!

473
00:39:09,010 --> 00:39:10,010
Shut it.

474
00:39:10,280 --> 00:39:13,580
To think she was born
just to bring shame to this family.

475
00:39:14,920 --> 00:39:16,250
There are many other victims.

476
00:39:16,790 --> 00:39:19,060
And they will all carry
those deep scars for life.

477
00:39:20,220 --> 00:39:21,560
Okay, we understand.

478
00:39:22,160 --> 00:39:24,660
We'll punish her severely
so she never does it again.

479
00:39:25,300 --> 00:39:28,530
But it's the middle of the night,
and with his blood pressure...

480
00:39:28,600 --> 00:39:30,330
The reason I came all this way is this.

481
00:39:33,200 --> 00:39:35,040
I want you to hit her ten times,
right in front of me.

482
00:39:36,770 --> 00:39:41,080
Or, I'll hit her myself, just as much
as Seong Tae's crew hit me today,

483
00:39:41,380 --> 00:39:43,050
and I'll turn myself in to the police.

484
00:39:46,980 --> 00:39:47,990
To be honest,

485
00:39:49,050 --> 00:39:50,690
I don't really have much to live for.

486
00:39:53,290 --> 00:39:55,690
Just like Ye Jeong taunted me
and hit me where it hurt,

487
00:39:56,760 --> 00:39:58,230
my own parents abandoned me.

488
00:39:59,300 --> 00:40:01,400
So why would I have any will to live
or attachment to my life?

489
00:40:03,300 --> 00:40:06,600
I grew up never once getting
to say "Mom" or "Dad" like everyone else.

490
00:40:07,440 --> 00:40:10,210
Can any of you even imagine
how that feels?

491
00:40:12,510 --> 00:40:14,610
I only hit you back a few times
in self-defense.

492
00:40:15,150 --> 00:40:18,680
You got so mad over a couple of hits
you sent your thug "husband" after me.

493
00:40:19,880 --> 00:40:24,050
I don't know if he's really your man
or if it's just for show.

494
00:40:25,120 --> 00:40:27,020
You shouldn't just say things like that...

495
00:40:27,090 --> 00:40:29,460
You've done a fine job
raising your only daughter.

496
00:40:31,830 --> 00:40:33,360
Try to imagine how the kids...

497
00:40:34,130 --> 00:40:35,530
you tormented and beat up must feel.

498
00:40:36,630 --> 00:40:40,040
They've likely imagined tearing you apart
a thousand times over in their minds.

499
00:40:41,970 --> 00:40:43,140
Because that's what I was doing today.

500
00:40:45,480 --> 00:40:46,780
I barely held myself back...

501
00:40:48,210 --> 00:40:49,610
and came here to deal
with this rationally.

502
00:40:51,250 --> 00:40:52,320
I'm sorry.

503
00:40:52,450 --> 00:40:53,650
We understand, so please go.

504
00:40:54,550 --> 00:40:56,850
- Something like today will never...
- You can't even hit her ten times?

505
00:40:57,960 --> 00:41:00,890
We'll discuss it
and discipline her ourselves.

506
00:41:01,020 --> 00:41:02,060
In front of me.

507
00:41:04,660 --> 00:41:05,660
Only then,

508
00:41:06,900 --> 00:41:08,070
I think I'll be able to live with this.

509
00:41:09,630 --> 00:41:11,140
Go get me something.

510
00:41:12,900 --> 00:41:13,900
Hurry up.

511
00:41:14,810 --> 00:41:17,610
There's nothing suitable here.
I'll have something prepared by tomorrow.

512
00:41:17,670 --> 00:41:19,910
- We have the golf club.
- Father!

513
00:41:20,180 --> 00:41:21,180
I was wrong!

514
00:41:21,250 --> 00:41:24,680
If saying you were wrong could erase
the scars and injuries I have,

515
00:41:25,720 --> 00:41:26,720
I'd accept your apology.

516
00:41:31,690 --> 00:41:34,530
You hit her ten times.

517
00:41:34,890 --> 00:41:38,500
- Father!
- You hit her ten times,

518
00:41:39,830 --> 00:41:41,670
and her father will get a beating from me.

519
00:41:43,000 --> 00:41:45,200
You need to see this with your own eyes.

520
00:41:45,340 --> 00:41:46,640
All because of this one girl!

521
00:41:46,700 --> 00:41:48,940
Grandfather, I'll turn over a new leaf.
Starting today.

522
00:41:49,010 --> 00:41:50,710
What exactly is your relationship
with that punk?

523
00:41:50,970 --> 00:41:52,180
You're not even dry behind the ears.

524
00:41:52,510 --> 00:41:54,410
Please, I swear.

525
00:41:54,480 --> 00:41:57,010
He just always acts like he's flirting.

526
00:41:57,250 --> 00:41:58,620
There's nothing going on between us.

527
00:41:58,620 --> 00:42:00,320
He's just a bodyguard.

528
00:42:00,420 --> 00:42:02,320
If my orphanage friend
hadn't been there today,

529
00:42:02,320 --> 00:42:03,750
who knows what would've happened?

530
00:42:03,820 --> 00:42:06,160
- They were trying to strip me...
- Hey! Get over here. Now.

531
00:42:06,220 --> 00:42:07,220
Dad, I'm sorry! I was wrong!

532
00:42:07,490 --> 00:42:10,590
- Honey.
- What a fine mess this family is in.

533
00:42:10,890 --> 00:42:12,900
You feed her well,
dress her in nice clothes,

534
00:42:13,100 --> 00:42:16,000
and you think just throwing money
at her studies is how you raise a child?

535
00:42:16,400 --> 00:42:17,400
Darn it.

536
00:42:17,670 --> 00:42:18,800
- Grandfather!
- Honey.

537
00:42:20,400 --> 00:42:22,470
- Grandfather.
- Father.

538
00:42:24,370 --> 00:42:26,410
No, honey, you have to stop him.

539
00:42:47,930 --> 00:42:49,230
Maybe it was karma,

540
00:42:50,870 --> 00:42:52,840
but two months later, Tae Ye Jeong died.

541
00:42:54,240 --> 00:42:55,940
At their vacation home on Jeju Island,

542
00:42:57,110 --> 00:42:58,280
on the beach right in front of the house.

543
00:43:02,810 --> 00:43:05,820
Because I didn't have parents
and grew up in an orphanage,

544
00:43:07,150 --> 00:43:10,350
I went through so much
and was always looked down on.

545
00:43:12,320 --> 00:43:14,860
Sometimes I wonder
if the expressions I show people...

546
00:43:15,590 --> 00:43:16,630
and the emotions I display...

547
00:43:17,690 --> 00:43:20,400
are all just an act.

548
00:43:23,400 --> 00:43:25,000
When I felt so worthless,

549
00:43:25,640 --> 00:43:27,570
there were people
who genuinely cared for me.

550
00:43:29,270 --> 00:43:30,270
There was An Hee,

551
00:43:31,840 --> 00:43:32,840
and there was you.

552
00:43:36,450 --> 00:43:38,950
An Hee took care of me
because we were in the same boat,

553
00:43:39,920 --> 00:43:40,920
but you...

554
00:43:42,150 --> 00:43:44,150
genuinely adored me when I was just a kid.

555
00:43:47,220 --> 00:43:49,460
It was the first time
I had ever really felt it.

556
00:43:49,960 --> 00:43:53,000
"Oh, so this is what it's like
to be adored."

557
00:43:54,830 --> 00:43:56,030
It was only for a few months, but...

558
00:44:00,740 --> 00:44:03,840
I've always missed that warmth.

559
00:44:04,810 --> 00:44:06,740
Thinking of it helped me
get through the hard times.

560
00:44:14,590 --> 00:44:15,590
So even if you...

561
00:44:16,620 --> 00:44:19,090
like and love a wicked witch,

562
00:44:21,360 --> 00:44:23,690
I feel like it's my place
to try to understand.

563
00:44:25,500 --> 00:44:27,000
Maybe no one else has to,

564
00:44:29,170 --> 00:44:30,170
but I do.

565
00:44:39,340 --> 00:44:40,340
I'll always...

566
00:44:41,950 --> 00:44:42,950
be by your side.

567
00:44:44,580 --> 00:44:46,180
We'll never be apart again.

568
00:44:48,090 --> 00:44:49,090
Forever?

569
00:44:50,950 --> 00:44:51,960
Forever.

570
00:44:53,360 --> 00:44:55,090
You don't have to force it.

571
00:44:56,260 --> 00:44:57,290
I'm not.

572
00:44:58,900 --> 00:45:02,530
My brother and I aren't related by blood,
but he's the only brother I have.

573
00:45:05,400 --> 00:45:06,400
It's the same with you.

574
00:45:09,010 --> 00:45:10,170
Just promise me one thing.

575
00:45:12,240 --> 00:45:13,280
What?

576
00:45:13,280 --> 00:45:14,680
When things get tough and you struggle,

577
00:45:16,180 --> 00:45:17,710
don't try to bear it all on your own.

578
00:45:18,950 --> 00:45:20,250
You've got me now.

579
00:45:21,550 --> 00:45:23,150
I'll be content with just having you...

580
00:45:24,350 --> 00:45:26,290
by my side or watching from afar.

581
00:45:28,090 --> 00:45:29,160
My dear Ba Ra...

582
00:45:30,460 --> 00:45:32,100
You've done so well for yourself.

583
00:45:34,230 --> 00:45:35,830
The more I think about it,
the prouder I am of you,

584
00:45:38,440 --> 00:45:39,440
and I'm so grateful.

585
00:45:45,580 --> 00:45:47,480
Why'd An Hee have to die,
leaving us behind?

586
00:45:48,450 --> 00:45:50,050
Imagine how great it would be
if he were with us now.

587
00:45:54,020 --> 00:45:55,390
I have a favor to ask, too.

588
00:45:57,050 --> 00:45:58,060
What is it?

589
00:45:58,660 --> 00:45:59,920
Live a long, long life.

590
00:46:01,790 --> 00:46:02,790
Promise me.

591
00:46:06,700 --> 00:46:07,700
All right.

592
00:46:08,670 --> 00:46:10,730
I have to grant any wish
my big girl asks of me.

593
00:46:12,840 --> 00:46:14,540
Just don't ask for the moon.

594
00:46:15,610 --> 00:46:17,370
Some things are just impossible.

595
00:46:32,090 --> 00:46:33,460
If you find her,

596
00:46:33,790 --> 00:46:35,830
tell her...

597
00:46:36,530 --> 00:46:37,530
that her mom was so, so sorry.

598
00:46:43,900 --> 00:46:46,240
You have to find her. No matter what.

599
00:46:57,950 --> 00:46:59,880
You've been on a real roll lately.

600
00:47:00,250 --> 00:47:02,120
It's been one Geum Ba Ra exclusive
after another.

601
00:47:08,020 --> 00:47:10,730
(A sentence can change the world.
Relentless pursuit of truth)

602
00:47:13,200 --> 00:47:14,200
Get in.

603
00:47:17,300 --> 00:47:19,000
(A sentence can change the world.
Relentless pursuit of truth)

604
00:47:19,500 --> 00:47:21,440
The other outlets are busy
just copying each other's stories,

605
00:47:24,110 --> 00:47:28,150
and since you're so short-staffed,
it must be hard just to keep up.

606
00:47:28,210 --> 00:47:29,210
You're doing a great job.

607
00:47:29,480 --> 00:47:30,480
Not at all, sir.

608
00:47:31,050 --> 00:47:32,450
I'm keeping an eye on you.

609
00:47:33,320 --> 00:47:34,320
Thank you, sir.

610
00:47:35,750 --> 00:47:38,660
Sorry, Yong Joong.
I just got an urgent assignment.

611
00:47:39,390 --> 00:47:40,820
Don't apologize to me.

612
00:47:42,960 --> 00:47:43,960
Okay?

613
00:47:45,060 --> 00:47:46,060
Alright.

614
00:47:46,560 --> 00:47:48,100
And you've picked up another cute habit.

615
00:47:50,800 --> 00:47:53,600
At some point,
you dropped the formalities with me.

616
00:47:54,470 --> 00:47:56,810
My gosh, what's gotten into me?

617
00:47:57,110 --> 00:47:58,110
That's why I like it.

618
00:47:59,080 --> 00:48:00,210
You think I'm a pushover, don't you?

619
00:48:00,810 --> 00:48:01,810
No, that's not it.

620
00:48:02,110 --> 00:48:03,110
Try that again.

621
00:48:04,750 --> 00:48:05,750
No.

622
00:48:05,750 --> 00:48:07,550
I'm the guy
you're most comfortable being with.

623
00:48:11,890 --> 00:48:12,890
Get back to it.

624
00:48:13,960 --> 00:48:15,130
Yes.

625
00:48:15,130 --> 00:48:16,290
"Yes?"

626
00:48:16,590 --> 00:48:17,860
Okay, Yong Joong.

627
00:48:19,400 --> 00:48:20,400
You hang up first.

628
00:48:21,200 --> 00:48:22,400
Here's your coffee.

629
00:49:00,070 --> 00:49:01,070
Welcome.

630
00:49:05,280 --> 00:49:06,280
Here...

631
00:49:07,810 --> 00:49:10,950
Should I put this in the fridge for now?
Is there room?

632
00:49:12,350 --> 00:49:14,520
I'll sort it out and put it away...

633
00:49:16,190 --> 00:49:17,250
Have you been eating properly?

634
00:49:18,920 --> 00:49:20,790
Don't you have anyone you can call?

635
00:49:21,590 --> 00:49:22,730
My manager stops by every now and then...

636
00:49:26,960 --> 00:49:27,960
What about Ju Shin?

637
00:49:29,630 --> 00:49:31,740
How about staying somewhere else
for a little while?

638
00:49:36,710 --> 00:49:37,770
We're...

639
00:49:38,780 --> 00:49:40,210
all in the same boat.

640
00:49:41,410 --> 00:49:43,550
Ju Shin, you,

641
00:49:44,380 --> 00:49:45,450
and me.

642
00:49:47,620 --> 00:49:48,750
Someone once said...

643
00:49:49,790 --> 00:49:51,550
that if you don't have parents,
you're an orphan.

644
00:49:52,920 --> 00:49:55,830
When did your parents pass away?

645
00:49:56,990 --> 00:49:58,700
My dad passed away
when I was in second grade.

646
00:50:00,060 --> 00:50:01,260
And my mom passed away
during my senior year of high school.

647
00:50:02,000 --> 00:50:04,170
So I know how you feel
better than anyone, Momo.

648
00:50:06,170 --> 00:50:07,640
I know how hard it must be
for you right now.

649
00:50:17,410 --> 00:50:20,450
When my mother passed away,
I couldn't even really cry.

650
00:50:22,320 --> 00:50:23,650
My brother cried a lot, though.

651
00:50:25,160 --> 00:50:26,720
Isn't this the part
where he gives me a hug?

652
00:50:37,070 --> 00:50:38,940
Did Ju Shin tell you about my brother?

653
00:50:41,070 --> 00:50:44,540
James told me himself once.

654
00:50:45,410 --> 00:50:47,880
That he was adopted in elementary school.

655
00:50:52,020 --> 00:50:55,350
I heard James's birth mother
and your mother...

656
00:50:56,190 --> 00:50:58,690
were in the same orchestra, right?

657
00:50:59,020 --> 00:51:00,020
Yes.

658
00:51:03,660 --> 00:51:05,260
It might sound like a cliche,
but it's true.

659
00:51:06,330 --> 00:51:07,630
As time goes on,

660
00:51:08,900 --> 00:51:10,330
the sadness does fade.

661
00:51:12,340 --> 00:51:14,040
For now, all you can do is endure it.

662
00:51:14,570 --> 00:51:15,770
There's no other way.

663
00:51:19,710 --> 00:51:20,780
Thank you.

664
00:51:31,450 --> 00:51:34,660
I bought the Laketop penthouse.
Would you like to stay there for a while?

665
00:51:35,490 --> 00:51:36,730
What's the point of leaving it empty?

666
00:51:36,730 --> 00:51:39,000
I was worried tenants would ruin it,
so it's empty.

667
00:51:40,300 --> 00:51:43,500
The 18-million-dollar Laketop penthouse?

668
00:51:49,040 --> 00:51:50,070
Goodbye.

669
00:51:50,310 --> 00:51:51,780
Think about it and text me.

670
00:51:53,580 --> 00:51:54,580
Okay.

671
00:52:13,930 --> 00:52:15,070
Yes!

672
00:52:20,500 --> 00:52:23,510
That was the most delicious breakfast
I've had in a long time.

673
00:52:23,770 --> 00:52:24,840
Thank you.

674
00:52:29,180 --> 00:52:32,250
- What's got you in such a good mood?
- It's Ms. Geum Ba Ra.

675
00:52:32,580 --> 00:52:33,920
She said she loved my cooking.

676
00:52:33,980 --> 00:52:37,120
You would've made a killing
in the restaurant business.

677
00:52:37,390 --> 00:52:39,520
You dote on your brother,

678
00:52:39,520 --> 00:52:40,890
so no wonder
he doesn't think about getting married.

679
00:52:41,190 --> 00:52:42,390
He has everything he needs.

680
00:52:43,730 --> 00:52:45,630
How many of our pieces got into
Sera Lauren magazine?

681
00:52:48,470 --> 00:52:50,400
(Ha Yong Joong, CEO of WorldNet)

682
00:52:53,840 --> 00:52:57,410
(Ha Yong Joong, Developer of
Record-Breaking Mega-Hit "Lost Knights")

683
00:53:03,250 --> 00:53:04,280
(Ba Ra)

684
00:53:04,380 --> 00:53:06,020
I know this must be really hard,

685
00:53:06,780 --> 00:53:08,520
but people are curious.

686
00:53:09,090 --> 00:53:11,820
So it'd be good to briefly announce
your future plans.

687
00:53:12,620 --> 00:53:14,520
That should quiet down the media, too.

688
00:53:15,460 --> 00:53:17,260
I can drop by for a bit,

689
00:53:17,660 --> 00:53:19,630
or we could meet somewhere
you're comfortable.

690
00:53:23,000 --> 00:53:24,170
Are you getting any sleep?

691
00:53:25,670 --> 00:53:28,440
Only a little after I've completely
exhausted myself.

692
00:53:30,110 --> 00:53:31,410
Are you cleaning up her things alone?

693
00:53:34,280 --> 00:53:35,610
I'd like to help.

694
00:53:36,350 --> 00:53:37,350
I'm okay.

695
00:53:39,480 --> 00:53:41,250
Last year, on the day we were
supposed to meet,

696
00:53:41,650 --> 00:53:44,420
I saw your mother at the airport,
and she was so cheerful.

697
00:53:45,760 --> 00:53:48,190
Did you have any idea she was struggling?

698
00:53:52,000 --> 00:53:54,700
Then why did you cut off all contact
for so long...

699
00:53:56,100 --> 00:53:59,370
The moment I let my guard down,
I got burnt out.

700
00:54:01,040 --> 00:54:02,870
I spent a few months in Lausanne, too.

701
00:54:04,410 --> 00:54:05,540
Lausanne, in Switzerland?

702
00:54:08,910 --> 00:54:10,350
I need you to run a story
on my retirement.

703
00:54:11,980 --> 00:54:14,220
Wouldn't it be better to keep busy?

704
00:54:15,150 --> 00:54:16,290
I don't have it in me.

705
00:54:16,820 --> 00:54:17,820
Who would I even be doing it for...?

706
00:54:18,690 --> 00:54:20,320
Your fans are going to be so disappointed.

707
00:54:22,990 --> 00:54:24,960
Is your wedding with Director Shin
still on?

708
00:54:26,560 --> 00:54:28,000
You don't have to talk about it
if you don't want to.

709
00:54:28,800 --> 00:54:30,370
It's just so absurd.

710
00:54:31,070 --> 00:54:32,640
Professor Shin, who was so healthy...

711
00:54:36,210 --> 00:54:39,610
I mean, Ju Shin's father
passed away so suddenly,

712
00:54:40,540 --> 00:54:41,640
and now my mom, too.

713
00:54:44,510 --> 00:54:46,320
Does your head hurt?
Should I get you something for it?

714
00:54:46,320 --> 00:54:47,420
No, I have some.

715
00:54:48,020 --> 00:54:50,520
I'm not in a good state,
so if I'm not around much...

716
00:54:52,660 --> 00:54:54,890
I understand. Take your time to heal.

717
00:54:56,990 --> 00:54:58,260
Yong Joong stopped by, didn't he?

718
00:54:59,500 --> 00:55:01,160
Are you that close? Are you dating?

719
00:55:03,470 --> 00:55:07,170
He's an old friend from the orphanage.
We were best friends in high school.

720
00:55:07,800 --> 00:55:09,640
I've told you this before.

721
00:55:14,010 --> 00:55:15,880
My brain is completely fried.

722
00:55:17,010 --> 00:55:18,510
I even forget to eat.

723
00:55:31,090 --> 00:55:33,800
To be honest,
her condition was critical at first.

724
00:55:33,960 --> 00:55:36,930
She only recovered because Director Shin
kept her on hyperbaric oxygen therapy.

725
00:55:37,330 --> 00:55:38,430
How bad was it?

726
00:55:38,640 --> 00:55:41,200
I never saw her myself.
I heard it from one of the executives.

727
00:55:41,970 --> 00:55:43,340
Is she really going to retire?

728
00:55:44,140 --> 00:55:47,480
Yes.
Has Director Choi told you differently?

729
00:55:48,440 --> 00:55:49,450
(Ha Yong Joong: "Lost Knights" Creator)

730
00:55:49,510 --> 00:55:51,350
(Actress Momo Suddenly Retires.
Agency Respects Her Wishes.)

731
00:55:51,450 --> 00:55:52,920
Looks like Geum Ba Ra
landed another scoop.

732
00:55:53,380 --> 00:55:55,520
- What is it?
- Momo announced her retirement.

733
00:55:55,850 --> 00:55:56,850
My gosh!

734
00:55:57,350 --> 00:56:00,060
(Actress Momo, 26, suddenly announced
her retirement from acting this afternoon)

735
00:56:00,120 --> 00:56:03,190
(Nua General Hospital)

736
00:56:03,260 --> 00:56:05,430
(Nua General Hospital)

737
00:56:05,500 --> 00:56:06,600
(Neurosurgery)

738
00:56:14,740 --> 00:56:18,570
Could you please give this
to Director Shin?

739
00:56:34,220 --> 00:56:35,430
Do you like the painting?

740
00:56:37,590 --> 00:56:39,060
It's a Paul Kim, isn't it?

741
00:56:43,630 --> 00:56:44,800
Take that painting down.

742
00:56:45,740 --> 00:56:47,700
- Why? It's a nice piece.
- I'm giving it to Reporter Geum.

743
00:56:51,770 --> 00:56:52,780
Hey.

744
00:56:54,940 --> 00:56:56,450
You don't have feelings for Ba Ra, do you?

745
00:57:01,620 --> 00:57:03,920
- You do?
- I've thought about it.

746
00:57:04,720 --> 00:57:06,560
You know I have a thing for smart women.

747
00:57:07,020 --> 00:57:08,090
Are you crazy?

748
00:57:08,660 --> 00:57:10,990
Are you out of your mind? You're 50!

749
00:57:11,090 --> 00:57:12,230
So what if I'm 50?

750
00:57:12,360 --> 00:57:14,160
Age is just a number.

751
00:57:14,160 --> 00:57:15,200
It's a very important number.

752
00:57:15,260 --> 00:57:17,830
People think I'm in my late thirties.

753
00:57:18,670 --> 00:57:19,870
You believe that flattery?

754
00:57:19,870 --> 00:57:22,140
In ten years, you'll be 60.

755
00:57:22,210 --> 00:57:24,140
- And Ba Ra's in her 30s.
- Her late 30s.

756
00:57:24,870 --> 00:57:27,680
Snap out of it.
She's not the right person for you.

757
00:57:27,780 --> 00:57:29,010
Don't you even think about it.

758
00:57:30,710 --> 00:57:32,380
There are plenty of other smart women
out there.

759
00:57:32,850 --> 00:57:35,490
Professor Lee Jin Hee, Dr. Shin...
Didn't you say they were both interested?

760
00:57:35,550 --> 00:57:36,920
But I'm the one who has to be attracted.

761
00:57:37,790 --> 00:57:39,320
That's greedy.

762
00:57:39,320 --> 00:57:40,990
How could you go for Ba Ra?
She could be your daughter.

763
00:57:41,160 --> 00:57:43,230
Look at actors in Hollywood.
It's the new trend.

764
00:57:43,660 --> 00:57:46,560
Find a better trend to follow.
You're no Hollywood star.

765
00:57:46,630 --> 00:57:47,830
Hey, I'm quite the catch.

766
00:57:48,430 --> 00:57:51,200
James of Lim Company.
Everyone in the industry knows who I am.

767
00:57:51,570 --> 00:57:53,840
Please stop. Don't embarrass yourself.

768
00:57:54,100 --> 00:57:55,910
Fortune favors the bold.

769
00:57:55,970 --> 00:57:57,540
- James.
- You just don't want to have...

770
00:57:57,540 --> 00:57:59,110
to call her your sister-in-law, do you?

771
00:57:59,710 --> 00:58:00,940
You've really got a problem.

772
00:58:01,510 --> 00:58:04,780
That's rich. You fell head over heels
for your best friend's fiancee.

773
00:58:04,850 --> 00:58:05,880
It's not like I knew who she was!

774
00:58:06,550 --> 00:58:08,550
Either way, don't drag me into this mess.

775
00:58:10,690 --> 00:58:14,620
How'd you feel if a woman 23 years older
than you threw herself at you?

776
00:58:14,690 --> 00:58:16,090
It's different for men and women.

777
00:58:16,860 --> 00:58:18,490
You'll get torn to shreds if you do that.

778
00:58:22,900 --> 00:58:25,300
I don't care if they drag me
through the mud.

779
00:58:28,300 --> 00:58:31,410
(True correction, bright future)

780
00:58:51,630 --> 00:58:54,600
Before my mom passed away,

781
00:58:54,700 --> 00:58:56,970
she told me I had an older sister.

782
00:58:57,870 --> 00:58:59,000
It was like a deathbed confession.

783
00:59:01,170 --> 00:59:03,240
Back when you two were in high school.

784
00:59:06,810 --> 00:59:08,310
So you haven't found her yet?

785
00:59:11,480 --> 00:59:12,680
It's not that simple.

786
00:59:14,380 --> 00:59:15,450
In any case,

787
00:59:16,650 --> 00:59:19,090
I've never met her,
but you're my sister's father,

788
00:59:19,920 --> 00:59:21,420
and you used to be my mom's boyfriend.

789
00:59:22,690 --> 00:59:23,930
You don't have to be so formal with me.

790
00:59:28,000 --> 00:59:29,070
Did that...

791
00:59:29,930 --> 00:59:31,470
cause any conflict?

792
00:59:32,300 --> 00:59:33,300
No.

793
00:59:33,700 --> 00:59:36,110
It's not my place
to say anything about the past.

794
00:59:36,940 --> 00:59:38,170
I admit I was surprised.

795
00:59:39,440 --> 00:59:41,740
My father was much older than she was,

796
00:59:41,880 --> 00:59:44,280
so I had a vague inkling...

797
00:59:44,580 --> 00:59:45,850
that there was a backstory.

798
00:59:48,750 --> 00:59:50,620
If by some miracle we find her,

799
00:59:51,650 --> 00:59:56,160
I'd like to get along as sisters,
not just because my mom wanted us to.

800
00:59:56,690 --> 00:59:59,560
She's my only blood relative, after all.

801
01:00:01,030 --> 01:00:02,030
So please, let me know.

802
01:00:07,840 --> 01:00:08,940
You don't have to see me out.

803
01:00:32,360 --> 01:00:33,900
(Investigator Park)

804
01:00:42,740 --> 01:00:43,740
Hello?

805
01:00:44,710 --> 01:00:46,140
I believe we've found your daughter.

806
01:00:48,810 --> 01:00:49,810
Really?

807
01:01:15,370 --> 01:01:18,170
(Doctor Shin)

808
01:01:18,440 --> 01:01:19,440
Ladies first.

809
01:01:19,840 --> 01:01:21,310
This is our first day as a couple.

810
01:01:21,610 --> 01:01:23,410
- This is a bit of a weak celebration.
- It's more than enough.

811
01:01:23,480 --> 01:01:24,480
So I'm your number one?

812
01:01:25,250 --> 01:01:27,950
Don't tell me it's that Kim Jin Ju.

813
01:01:28,520 --> 01:01:30,950
- You're friends with Geum Ba Ra?
- Yes.

814
01:01:30,950 --> 01:01:32,290
Are both of you still single?

815
01:01:32,590 --> 01:01:34,560
- A boyfriend.
- Right.

816
01:01:34,620 --> 01:01:37,990
What if I only had eyes
for Director Shin Ju Shin?

817
01:01:38,060 --> 01:01:40,660
Shin Ju Shin is someone
women would fall for.

818
01:01:40,730 --> 01:01:43,670
- He's got it all.
- Hello, sir.

819
01:01:43,730 --> 01:01:45,130
You should brace yourself.

820
01:01:45,130 --> 01:01:46,140
Can I see her today?

821
01:01:46,200 --> 01:01:48,240
Is it because I'm thinking
about Momo too much?

822
01:01:48,870 --> 01:01:49,870
Sir.

823
01:01:51,540 --> 01:01:55,240
I just wish I had someone
I could give my all to.

824
01:01:55,480 --> 01:01:57,380
I gave you my heart

825
01:01:58,550 --> 01:02:00,820
I gave you my tears

826
01:02:01,380 --> 01:02:04,050
And I gave you my dreams

